comments.body:
@Luap99 I'm wondering if maybe you can shed any light on [all the 'podman stats' tests failures](https://storage.googleapis.com/cirrus-ci-6707778565701632-fcae48/artifacts/containers/podman/5171644936224768/html/int-podman-fedora-33-root-container.log.html)?  In your testing, did you by chance come across any of those 'cgroup deleted' errors anywhere?

Note: Your original 8b9b925e78cb1ef80a4d274b67611f48eb8f788d ran against VERY old F33 images, which I'm trying to update in this PR.  It's easily possible the more modern packages in the VM (and container) caused this to be missed.

Any help you can offer would be greatly appreciated.

> @cevich, is this still a WIP as the title claims?

Oh thank :godmode: finally, it passed with only 1 test re-run.

@containers/podman-maintainers PTAL - this is ready along with https://github.com/containers/podman/pull/11163
